Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges and solutions for conducting massive computational experiments in data science research. The primary focus is on the use of cloud computing and software stacks to simplify experimentation. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
